{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make it illegal to force staff to use their own credit card for company expenses",
        "additional_details": "Companies then take weeks to pay the expenses - and in a lot of cases refuse to pay interest - forcing the employee to fund the expenses through their own current account (to avoid the expenses charge).\r\n \r\nHaving these expenses hidden makes the company\u2019s balance sheet look more favourable than it is.\r\n \r\nIt is an abuse of the company\u2019s power and when employees challenge it they are told there is no choice; no other option.\r\n",
        "background": "More and more companies force / require employees to use their own funds and/or credit cards to fund company expenditure and to then claim back this expenditure after the fact.\r\n\r\nThe company's liability is then carried by the employee. \r\n\r\nThe employee is responsible to the credit card company.",
